WEBVTT

00:07.094 --> 00:09.052
Indira:
With the assistance of IO,

00:09.096 --> 00:12.273
the technology to save our world
is coming.

00:13.622 --> 00:15.450
The first wave is eager
to return to the mother.

00:15.493 --> 00:18.061
We've waited a long time
for this moment.

00:18.105 --> 00:19.410
Paul:
Why were you wondering

00:19.454 --> 00:22.152
the dark, deep woods at night,
lady?

00:22.196 --> 00:23.675
It's done.

00:23.719 --> 00:25.199
Why did you come up?

00:25.242 --> 00:26.678
[Laser pistol fires]

00:26.722 --> 00:28.854
[Grunting]

00:28.898 --> 00:30.508
I really wish
you wouldn't have seen this.

00:32.075 --> 00:33.250
I walked into something.

00:33.294 --> 00:35.426
I don't know who to trust.Trust me.

00:40.562 --> 00:42.303
- Trust me...

00:42.346 --> 00:44.131
[dramatic music]

00:44.174 --> 00:45.088
[dog barking]

00:45.132 --> 00:48.831
- [panting]

00:48.874 --> 00:51.790
[gentle music]

00:51.834 --> 00:57.100
♪

00:57.144 --> 01:00.103
[unsettling music]

01:00.147 --> 01:07.067
♪

01:14.770 --> 01:15.814
Ah!

01:17.903 --> 01:21.342
[gasps, coughs]

02:04.689 --> 02:06.952
- Thank you for your patience.

02:06.996 --> 02:09.346
Quite honestly,
I'm still in a state of shock.

02:09.390 --> 02:11.696
- We couldn't be
at a more delicate moment.

02:11.740 --> 02:14.046
The Bridge--
- I know how this looks.

02:14.090 --> 02:15.439
- Do you?

02:15.483 --> 02:17.049
Less than two weeks
until the First Wave

02:17.093 --> 02:19.356
arrives on Earth,
and someone tries to kill

02:19.400 --> 02:22.751
the Envoy's bodyguard
with a stolen drug.

02:22.794 --> 02:25.057
- Our government partnerships
remain strong,

02:25.101 --> 02:26.755
but on the street,
the extremist message

02:26.798 --> 02:28.191
is gaining ground.

02:28.235 --> 02:30.498
We anticipated an uptick
before Zero-day,

02:30.541 --> 02:31.629
but a story like this?

02:31.673 --> 02:33.370
It's already a tinderbox.

02:33.414 --> 02:36.199
- I agree.
It will be used to define us.

02:36.243 --> 02:38.201
- The story can be controlled.

02:38.245 --> 02:40.116
The question is,
can you control

02:40.160 --> 02:41.987
whatever is happening up there?

02:42.031 --> 02:43.902
We'd be fools to dismiss this
as a coincidence.

02:43.946 --> 02:45.426
- Agreed.

02:45.469 --> 02:47.297
Was this Terra?

02:47.341 --> 02:50.213
Have they finally found a way
to get an agent on Moonhaven?

02:50.257 --> 02:52.737
- Has Terra made any claims
on this incident?

02:52.781 --> 02:55.000
- We don't know
what happened yet.

02:55.044 --> 02:56.654
- Has the council chair
been dismissed?

02:58.917 --> 03:02.617
- I delivered the message.
She has yet to step down.

03:02.660 --> 03:04.923
- Ah...
- It's complicated.

03:04.967 --> 03:06.795
She has the support
of her people.

03:06.838 --> 03:10.233
- Indira, I don't want
to suggest the unthinkable,

03:10.277 --> 03:11.582
but isn't it possible

03:11.626 --> 03:13.584
the Mooners are turning
against us?

03:13.628 --> 03:16.587
- IO did predict a corruption
in the workflow.

03:16.631 --> 03:18.807
- If they were to find a way
to take control--

03:18.850 --> 03:22.941
- We are them, and they are us.

03:22.985 --> 03:24.421
- I know that's what we say--

03:24.465 --> 03:26.771
- For 100 years,
they've had one mission,

03:26.815 --> 03:28.382
one goal.

03:28.425 --> 03:30.253
These people have been raised
to think of nothing

03:30.297 --> 03:32.908
but solving our mess.

03:32.951 --> 03:34.823
The current council
will swap out,

03:34.866 --> 03:36.564
and a new council
will be named,

03:36.607 --> 03:39.741
and they will continue to do
what they have always done:

03:39.784 --> 03:42.874
devote their lives
to the future of our species,

03:42.918 --> 03:45.050
to the future of us.

03:45.094 --> 03:48.271
I will see
these troubles resolved.

03:48.315 --> 03:51.187
We will stay the course.

04:07.029 --> 04:09.988
[dramatic music]

04:10.032 --> 04:16.734
♪

04:55.033 --> 04:57.558
- All things change.

04:57.601 --> 04:59.516
[birds cawing]

04:59.560 --> 05:03.781
How we respond to change
is our choice.

05:03.825 --> 05:06.741
To fear it or embrace it.

05:06.784 --> 05:11.223
Resisting change leads only
to one fate:

05:11.267 --> 05:14.314
our own extinction.

05:14.357 --> 05:19.536
The Moon, a universal symbol
of freedom and peace.

05:19.580 --> 05:22.365
Chosen by ICON
as a setting to learn

05:22.409 --> 05:26.456
from the past in order to grow
toward a brighter future.

05:26.500 --> 05:28.937
The global mission
has developed IO,

05:28.980 --> 05:32.244
an unprecedented
machine-learning technology.

05:32.288 --> 05:34.290
The tool to repair
centuries of damage

05:34.334 --> 05:36.336
here on Earth,

05:36.379 --> 05:38.381
to bring home
real world solutions

05:38.425 --> 05:41.863
to problems
we had thought unsolvable.

05:41.906 --> 05:45.649
However, we cannot rely
entirely on technology.

05:45.693 --> 05:48.783
We, too, must evolve.

05:48.826 --> 05:52.047
Those on Moonhaven offer us
a new way of living,

05:52.090 --> 05:55.659
a bridge to peace, to health,
to the future,

05:55.703 --> 05:57.705
a path forward
that will not only begin

05:57.748 --> 06:01.752
to heal our Mother Earth,
but also ourselves.

06:01.796 --> 06:04.494
The Bridge offers us each
a second chance

06:04.538 --> 06:07.671
to play a crucial part
in its success.

06:07.715 --> 06:11.153
On the brink of this new dawn,
ask yourself.

06:11.196 --> 06:13.503
What will the Bridge mean
to you?

06:53.369 --> 06:56.328
[dramatic music]

06:56.372 --> 07:03.205
♪

07:22.616 --> 07:25.488
[birds chirping]

07:41.330 --> 07:44.115
[soft string music playing]

07:59.043 --> 08:00.958
- The ships
to take you to Earth--

08:01.002 --> 08:03.961
- In orbit.
I saw them.

08:04.005 --> 08:06.137
Waiting for permission to land,
I guess.

08:08.270 --> 08:10.664
- Your music--take it with you
when you go.

08:10.707 --> 08:11.969
A piece of us.

08:14.232 --> 08:16.060
I would be afraid
to be so far away.

08:16.104 --> 08:18.236
That sound would give me
sweet-smile.

08:18.280 --> 08:19.629
- I'm not afraid.

08:27.811 --> 08:30.771
[gentle music]

08:30.814 --> 08:32.903
♪

08:32.947 --> 08:34.122
- Paul.

08:41.346 --> 08:45.046
Our boy's gonna be gone
forever soon.

08:45.089 --> 08:47.352
- We still have time.

08:47.396 --> 08:49.572
We'll make the days
we have left sing.

08:49.616 --> 08:51.182
Everyone drifts
in their own time.

08:55.143 --> 08:56.666
- You're going back
to the Earther.

08:56.710 --> 08:59.408
- The man who killed her sister
is dead.

08:59.451 --> 09:01.323
The truth is hidden.

09:01.366 --> 09:02.890
Bella is her name.

09:02.933 --> 09:04.065
- They're dangerous.

09:04.108 --> 09:05.719
- They are us.

09:05.762 --> 09:07.503
We are them.

09:07.547 --> 09:10.201
"The future is better"
is not just words and thinks.

09:10.245 --> 09:11.376
It's the only way through.

09:14.336 --> 09:15.337
- Gleam.

09:25.042 --> 09:28.132
[tender music]

09:28.176 --> 09:35.052
♪

09:52.853 --> 09:54.071
- I didn't know
you were still there.

10:02.253 --> 10:03.428
- Take care today.

10:29.019 --> 10:30.107
- Bella?

10:40.596 --> 10:44.034
[dramatic music]

10:44.078 --> 10:45.122
- Ah!

10:45.166 --> 10:47.603
Where the hell am I?

10:47.647 --> 10:49.387
- I brought you here
to keep you safe.

10:49.431 --> 10:52.216
[intense music]

10:52.260 --> 10:58.266
♪

10:58.309 --> 10:59.702
- Son of a bitch.

10:59.746 --> 11:02.313
[panting]

11:02.357 --> 11:03.663
- You made a mess.

11:03.706 --> 11:06.448
- Sorry. I don't cage well.

11:06.491 --> 11:08.145
- I'll tell you
what you want to know.

11:11.845 --> 11:13.629
- Is this your idea
of a prison?

11:18.025 --> 11:19.809
- These are Scapes.

11:19.853 --> 11:23.160
Privacy huts for everyone.

11:23.204 --> 11:24.814
- Why did you bring me here?

11:24.858 --> 11:27.861
- Hmm. Frustangle.

11:27.904 --> 11:29.297
- The what?

11:31.081 --> 11:34.258
Frustangle, uh, it's a--a knot.

11:34.302 --> 11:36.521
A knot you don't know
how to untie.

11:36.565 --> 11:39.220
Felt it last night.

11:39.263 --> 11:42.571
Envoy's bodyguard overdosed
with stolen Singer.

11:42.614 --> 11:43.746
A Mooner shot.

11:46.793 --> 11:49.230
- So use your machine.

11:49.273 --> 11:51.449
Wave it over everybody
and get your answer.

11:51.493 --> 11:52.886
- Mm.

11:52.929 --> 11:54.496
The ship's
in a diplomatic blind.

11:54.539 --> 11:56.846
IO can't help.

11:56.890 --> 11:58.979
That's why the gun worked.

11:59.022 --> 12:01.372
You're the only one
who knows what happened, Bella.

12:01.416 --> 12:04.288
Did you know it was Strega Nall
who got shot,

12:04.332 --> 12:06.247
the man who killed your sister?

12:06.290 --> 12:07.727
- No.

12:07.770 --> 12:09.424
- What did you see?

12:09.467 --> 12:12.514
- I got back to CAT,

12:12.557 --> 12:15.473
and he had the needle
in Tomm's neck.

12:15.517 --> 12:19.651
But Tomm got a shot off
before he collapsed.

12:19.695 --> 12:21.958
- Singer's very powerful,

12:22.002 --> 12:24.091
very hard to get.

12:24.134 --> 12:26.484
- You think someone was trying
to steal the Singer.

12:26.528 --> 12:31.185
Was Chill caught
in some kind of drug deal?

12:31.228 --> 12:33.491
And what about that kid
we chased in the forest?

12:35.493 --> 12:36.364
- Frustangle.

12:40.324 --> 12:42.587
And you saw
every struggle and gasp.

12:45.025 --> 12:47.723
- I just want to get back
to my ship.

12:47.767 --> 12:50.726
It's damaged, but I can fix it.

12:50.770 --> 12:54.817
If you're holding me here
to heal me, Paul...

12:54.861 --> 12:59.343
- Hasn't been a murder here
in a long time.

12:59.387 --> 13:02.042
Now there are two.
- And I'm an Earther.

13:02.085 --> 13:03.521
You suspect me.

13:06.698 --> 13:09.179
- Just sit tight

13:09.223 --> 13:11.616
until Arlo and I figure out
what's going on.

13:11.660 --> 13:13.618
- Jesus, then I'll die here.

13:17.884 --> 13:20.974
You said two murders.
Don't you mean three?

13:21.017 --> 13:23.498
- Well,
there is some good news.

13:23.541 --> 13:26.675
IO was able to revive Tomm.

13:26.718 --> 13:29.634
His mind is far away,
and his body barely beats,

13:29.678 --> 13:30.635
but he will get better.

13:32.333 --> 13:34.074
Maybe he'll be able to tell us
what we don't know.

13:36.511 --> 13:38.469
Your ship, for now.

13:41.646 --> 13:44.258
- You make a better carpenter
than a detective.

13:44.301 --> 13:46.608
[soft music]

13:46.651 --> 13:49.045
- Enjoy. Relax.

13:49.089 --> 13:50.960
This is the Sea of Tranquility.

14:18.858 --> 14:21.425
- ♪ When the sweet wind

14:21.469 --> 14:25.125
♪ Did kiss the trees

14:25.168 --> 14:29.999
♪ And they did make no noise

14:31.348 --> 14:34.699
♪ In such night

14:37.528 --> 14:38.878
- Couldn't you
dream up something

14:38.921 --> 14:40.401
to do that for you?

14:40.444 --> 14:43.491
- These seeds
will bring bounty,

14:43.534 --> 14:45.972
food, medicines.

14:46.015 --> 14:49.323
Some can recover memory
or inspire.

14:49.366 --> 14:51.934
I yearn to be part
of such blessings.

14:51.978 --> 14:54.067
- Think of all the time
you'll have for blessings

14:54.110 --> 14:55.503
after your
council responsibilities

14:55.546 --> 14:56.504
are relinquished.

14:58.462 --> 15:01.988
- You spin in your loss, Envoy.

15:02.031 --> 15:03.293
A shock to us all.

15:03.337 --> 15:06.644
I hear your guard creeps
back to life.

15:06.688 --> 15:10.126
- Stabbed by a Mooner
trying to stow away

15:10.170 --> 15:12.563
with a stolen drug.
- Mm.

15:12.607 --> 15:16.219
- You've let chaos creep
into this place, Maite.

15:16.263 --> 15:20.484
IO saw it coming.
- Who knows what IO sees?

15:20.528 --> 15:23.748
It only said there was trouble
yet unspooled.

15:23.792 --> 15:26.142
Is this the trouble,

15:26.186 --> 15:29.319
or does something worse
lurk ahead?

15:29.363 --> 15:32.018
- ICON wants to know
this mess is cleaned up.

15:32.061 --> 15:33.758
They're expecting you
to step down.

15:33.802 --> 15:38.633
- [sighs] So quick
to guilt the Mooner.

15:38.676 --> 15:41.114
He's the one
who's gunned and dead.

15:41.157 --> 15:43.507
And what of the Earther pilot?

15:43.551 --> 15:46.249
- My pilot, Bella?
- A soldier, yes?

15:46.293 --> 15:50.253
- A cargo pilot,
thoroughly vetted.

15:50.297 --> 15:51.689
I haven't spoken to her yet.

15:51.733 --> 15:53.691
I was told
your people picked her up.

15:53.735 --> 15:56.216
- Our tectives
will see to her wellbeing.

15:56.259 --> 16:00.002
As for her story,
I've not heard what she said.

16:00.046 --> 16:02.352
But two Earthers live,

16:02.396 --> 16:04.702
and two Mooners lay dead.

16:04.746 --> 16:07.357
Who is left to speak for Lune?

16:07.401 --> 16:11.361
♪ Who speaks for me?

16:13.233 --> 16:16.932
- I will not have
the Bridge delayed.

16:16.976 --> 16:18.586
You will swap out.

16:18.629 --> 16:21.197
You will relinquish
your pass and key to IO

16:21.241 --> 16:24.548
to the next council chair.
- And if I don't?

16:24.592 --> 16:27.290
The two keys set the course
for IO.

16:27.334 --> 16:29.684
One from the Mother,
one from the Moon,

16:29.727 --> 16:32.339
as it has always been.

16:32.382 --> 16:33.993
You think
I'd step aside from that

16:34.036 --> 16:35.733
when my people need me most?

16:35.777 --> 16:38.432
- You will step down,
Maite Voss.

16:40.086 --> 16:42.044
I speak for the Earth.

16:42.088 --> 16:44.742
- Then you speak
for fragile order,

16:44.786 --> 16:48.833
desperation, tinder-wood,
and spark.

16:48.877 --> 16:50.444
How might Earth respond

16:50.487 --> 16:52.446
knowing her Bridge
to the better future

16:52.489 --> 16:55.144
now swing-sways

16:55.188 --> 16:58.060
in a perilous wind?

16:58.104 --> 17:01.063
[dramatic music]

17:01.107 --> 17:02.412
♪

17:02.456 --> 17:05.589
- You would leak this trouble?

17:05.633 --> 17:09.202
Destabilize everything
just to stay in power?

17:09.245 --> 17:12.074
- Only if you compel me.

17:12.118 --> 17:16.078
I won't let you frame this
as Moon trouble

17:16.122 --> 17:18.472
when it is of Earth.

17:18.515 --> 17:20.778
♪

17:53.115 --> 17:55.987
[device beeps]

17:57.989 --> 18:01.341
[device beeps]

18:01.384 --> 18:03.604
- Why do you bother?
He has no Mark.

18:03.647 --> 18:05.519
- I've never seen it
fail before.

18:05.562 --> 18:08.130
[device beeps]

18:08.174 --> 18:10.306
- We should look for clues,
Arlo.

18:10.350 --> 18:13.004
Try and deduce
what took place here.

18:13.048 --> 18:15.398
- Mm. Mm-hmm. Mm-hmm.

18:15.442 --> 18:16.921
- According to the witness,

18:16.965 --> 18:19.185
when she arrived,
she found Tomm and Strego

18:19.228 --> 18:20.882
already in a struggle.
- Mm-hmm.

18:20.925 --> 18:24.364
- Strego's weak and bleeding
from extracting his Mark.

18:24.407 --> 18:25.626
Wait, wait, wait.

18:25.669 --> 18:27.889
Don't touch.

18:27.932 --> 18:29.804
Fingerprints.

18:29.847 --> 18:31.849
- You know
how to check for those?

18:31.893 --> 18:34.983
- I might learn. Yeah.

18:35.026 --> 18:38.682
Okay, so Strego is much smaller
than the Earther.

18:38.726 --> 18:40.989
He's surprised,
so he stabs him...

18:41.032 --> 18:42.382
- Argh!
- With the Singer.

18:42.425 --> 18:45.689
- The Singer
which Strego stole

18:45.733 --> 18:48.257
and planned
to sneak back to Earth.

18:48.301 --> 18:49.780
- Perhaps.

18:49.824 --> 18:54.089
- Because that's
where his true love waits

18:54.133 --> 18:55.569
with his child.

18:55.612 --> 18:59.486
A child conceived through space

18:59.529 --> 19:02.706
by an ancient magic
of some sort.

19:02.750 --> 19:05.013
- So Strego stabs Tomm.

19:05.056 --> 19:08.277
- Yes,
and then Tomm shoots Strego.

19:08.321 --> 19:09.757
And then Bella arrives,

19:09.800 --> 19:12.455
and maybe it's she
who rips Strego's Mark out

19:12.499 --> 19:14.936
with her bare hands
in a blood frenzy.

19:14.979 --> 19:16.242
- Blood frenzy?
- Yes.

19:16.285 --> 19:17.895
An Earther might do that,
see the violence

19:17.939 --> 19:20.115
and lose control.

19:20.159 --> 19:22.944
- Could you deduce less, Arlo?
- Oh, I like deducing.

19:26.339 --> 19:29.733
Could this all be connected
to the death of Chill Spen?

19:29.777 --> 19:33.563
- Yes, yes.
- Mm?

19:33.607 --> 19:35.435
Chill and Strego
could have been planning

19:35.478 --> 19:37.219
to smuggle the drug.
- Mm-hmm.

19:37.263 --> 19:38.351
- But why would Strego
kill her?

19:38.394 --> 19:39.439
- Hmm.

19:39.482 --> 19:41.571
And why would he extract
his Mark?

19:41.615 --> 19:43.573
- So IO couldn't know
the dark he did.

19:43.617 --> 19:45.358
- No, he had it in the station
when we saw him.

19:45.401 --> 19:46.707
He must have taken it out
after.

19:46.750 --> 19:48.230
- Oh...
- What did he not want IO

19:48.274 --> 19:49.971
to see him do?
Hmm?

19:56.195 --> 19:57.457
- Something so bad

19:57.500 --> 19:58.849
that he'd want to leave
the Moon behind.

20:09.077 --> 20:12.602
- Have we ever had
such a lost soul?

20:14.691 --> 20:18.565
[dramatic music]

20:18.608 --> 20:21.611
- Where the fuck is my ship?

20:21.655 --> 20:27.878
♪

20:27.922 --> 20:30.272
- We need to learn more
about Strego.

20:30.316 --> 20:33.449
- Maybe Chill didn't like
Strego's darkness either.

20:33.493 --> 20:36.191
Maybe she knew too much.

20:38.454 --> 20:39.673
- That actually makes
some sense.

20:50.901 --> 20:53.295
How now, Orbis?

20:53.339 --> 20:55.036
- She misses her master still.

20:57.908 --> 21:00.302
- And you?

21:00.346 --> 21:01.999
How do you fare
with the loss, Asus?

21:02.043 --> 21:03.784
- The Bright has helped.

21:03.827 --> 21:05.264
Joy comes easy again.

21:07.178 --> 21:10.486
But in place of sadness,

21:10.530 --> 21:14.316
I'm giggle-headed
at the thought of my sister.

21:14.360 --> 21:18.407
She was here,
and now she's not.

21:20.670 --> 21:22.933
How can it be?

21:22.977 --> 21:28.025
- Well, without grief,
death is silly.

21:28.069 --> 21:30.027
We're everyall, then nothing.
It is absurd.

21:30.071 --> 21:31.246
- Mm-hmm.

21:34.380 --> 21:36.556
Chill and Strego,

21:36.599 --> 21:38.209
they fit well?

21:38.253 --> 21:40.124
She showed no shadow or cringe?

21:40.168 --> 21:44.477
- Nay, bloom and bright-light,
the both of them.

21:44.520 --> 21:46.392
They had hard days
and easy days,

21:46.435 --> 21:49.090
but the killing makes no sense.

21:49.133 --> 21:53.181
I should be lucky
to find a love so loyal-true.

21:53.224 --> 21:56.140
Why do many questions
about the dead, detective?

21:56.184 --> 21:58.447
Usually your concern
is with the living.

21:58.491 --> 22:00.406
- The situation leaves us
little choice.

22:00.449 --> 22:03.060
We find ourselves--
- Paul likes the Earther ways.

22:03.104 --> 22:05.585
We are solving the case.

22:08.762 --> 22:13.854
- And Strego
never had any doubts, worries?

22:13.897 --> 22:17.292
- He worried often
of the Bridge,

22:17.336 --> 22:20.208
of how different it will be
as we leave the Moon,

22:20.251 --> 22:23.037
whether the Earthers
will accept our ways.

22:23.080 --> 22:26.170
Who of us has no noggin-swirl
around this?

22:26.214 --> 22:28.042
- Why would he do it, Asus?

22:28.085 --> 22:30.392
- Does it matter why?

22:30.436 --> 22:32.612
Strego is dead.
Chill is dead.

22:32.655 --> 22:35.310
My grief is dealt.

22:35.354 --> 22:38.008
What of her blood-sister,
Bella?

22:38.052 --> 22:41.185
Have you done your job for her?
Your real job?

22:43.971 --> 22:45.146
Wait.

22:50.238 --> 22:53.067
Chill asked me to keep this
for her.

22:53.110 --> 22:55.461
She said
she was coming back for it.

23:00.161 --> 23:03.207
- Hmm, locked and sealed.

23:03.251 --> 23:05.906
- Mystery.
This is a clue, Paul.

23:05.949 --> 23:07.951
- Nay.

23:07.995 --> 23:10.780
I mean for you
to give it to Bella.

23:10.824 --> 23:12.521
A piece of her sister.

23:14.915 --> 23:17.439
Stop chasing the gonesouls,

23:17.483 --> 23:19.441
and get back to helping
those left behind.

23:19.485 --> 23:22.444
[soft music]

23:22.488 --> 23:29.364
♪

23:58.393 --> 24:01.352
[upbeat drumming]

24:01.396 --> 24:04.225
♪

24:04.268 --> 24:06.270
all: [chanting]
We are all one here!

24:06.314 --> 24:08.708
We are all one here!
We are all one here!

24:08.751 --> 24:11.145
What loss? Say do!

24:11.188 --> 24:14.104
- My Love lift today.

24:14.148 --> 24:16.367
all: Love lift to da light,
to da light!

24:16.411 --> 24:19.109
They that go can hear!

24:19.153 --> 24:20.981
Fly your voice, do!

24:21.024 --> 24:23.462
Your voice, your voice,
your voice, your voice!

24:23.505 --> 24:26.290
- [wailing]

24:43.656 --> 24:45.527
- Apologies for intruding,
Envoy.

24:45.571 --> 24:48.704
- It's quite all right.
Grats for coming.

24:48.748 --> 24:49.792
- Mm.

24:51.925 --> 24:54.405
How is he?
- IO's doing everything he can.

24:54.449 --> 24:56.538
He'll be moved
to the healing house today.

24:56.582 --> 24:58.366
- Ten Singers at once.

24:58.409 --> 25:00.586
- You can't go that far away
and still be what you were.

25:03.893 --> 25:05.765
The future is better.

25:07.157 --> 25:09.290
- Thank you.

25:09.333 --> 25:14.164
My pilot, Bella Sway.
You have her.

25:14.208 --> 25:16.079
- Uh, yes.

25:16.123 --> 25:18.038
- What did she see with Tomm?

25:18.081 --> 25:21.041
- Um, scuffle and grind.

25:21.084 --> 25:25.349
The stabbing and the shot.
I arrived soon after.

25:25.393 --> 25:29.223
- This incident complicates
everything.

25:29.266 --> 25:32.443
- We've spent some time
with her.

25:32.487 --> 25:34.141
I believe she tells the truth.

25:34.184 --> 25:37.318
- Then you know more about her
than I.

25:37.361 --> 25:40.103
We were slotted into her ship
at the last minute.

25:40.147 --> 25:41.844
Tomm checked her out.

25:46.153 --> 25:50.200
May I share something
in confidence?

25:50.244 --> 25:53.900
Because of what Moonhaven is,
because of who you are,

25:53.943 --> 25:56.293
IO is safe here.

25:56.337 --> 25:58.861
It learns from the best of us,
not the worst.

26:01.342 --> 26:03.910
No one on Earth has ever been
able to contaminate Lune

26:03.953 --> 26:06.042
with terror or greed.

26:06.086 --> 26:08.436
- We have terror and greed,
Madam Envoy.

26:08.479 --> 26:10.830
It is our job
to heal the wounds.

26:10.873 --> 26:15.138
- You have crimes of passion.
You are human.

26:15.182 --> 26:17.401
But true evil
has never set foot here.

26:20.883 --> 26:23.625
ICON is concerned
some Earth extremists

26:23.669 --> 26:26.585
have found a way to get
an agent on the Moon

26:26.628 --> 26:29.413
with the intent of preventing
the Bridge from moving forward.

26:32.199 --> 26:35.811
- This is bleak, Envoy,

26:35.855 --> 26:37.639
but still only in shadow.

26:37.683 --> 26:39.162
Nothing is known.

26:39.206 --> 26:41.382
- You think
the pilot is involved?

26:41.425 --> 26:42.775
- I want to believe
what happened on the ship

26:42.818 --> 26:44.646
was a random event,

26:44.690 --> 26:46.213
a crisis of judgment.

26:48.650 --> 26:50.870
I try to believe the best
in people, even at their worst.

26:50.913 --> 26:53.829
[dramatic music]

26:53.873 --> 27:00.749
♪

27:21.378 --> 27:22.771
[twig breaks]

27:55.674 --> 27:58.589
[Mooners humming]

27:58.633 --> 28:05.509
♪

28:10.601 --> 28:12.516
- What have you done
with my ship?

28:14.780 --> 28:17.043
I just want to go home.

28:17.086 --> 28:19.610
- We mean you no harm.

28:19.654 --> 28:21.830
But you can run no more.

28:49.553 --> 28:52.469
[gentle music]

28:52.513 --> 28:59.389
♪

29:05.308 --> 29:08.921
[explosions, radio chatter]

29:08.964 --> 29:11.880
[gunfire]

29:14.187 --> 29:16.755
- Contact, contact.
Armed. Inbound.

29:16.798 --> 29:19.453
- I have vis. Inbound.
Ten seconds.

29:19.496 --> 29:21.498
Heads up, Orion 334.

29:21.542 --> 29:23.370
Time out three. Target lock.

29:23.413 --> 29:26.590
- Closing. 3285 at 4K steady.

29:26.634 --> 29:28.505
- I see him.
Engage.

29:28.549 --> 29:30.812
- I've got new lights above.
- Heat lock, weapon away.

29:30.856 --> 29:32.553
- Lock, pilot, don't go.

29:32.596 --> 29:34.163
- Come round, come round,
Orion!

29:34.207 --> 29:36.426
- Warning. Warning.

29:54.444 --> 29:56.011
["Wild Is the Wind"
playing on music top]

29:56.055 --> 29:59.885
- ♪ Love me, love me,
love me ♪

29:59.928 --> 30:04.237
♪ Say you do

30:04.280 --> 30:08.850
♪

30:08.894 --> 30:15.770
♪ Let me fly away with you

30:15.814 --> 30:18.729
♪

30:18.773 --> 30:20.775
♪ For my love...

30:20.819 --> 30:23.517
- Your mother--
she was a Mooner.

30:23.560 --> 30:26.172
One of us.

30:26.215 --> 30:28.914
- I never knew my mother.

30:28.957 --> 30:33.527
I heard she decided
to come here after I was born.

30:33.570 --> 30:35.529
She left me behind.

30:35.572 --> 30:38.053
Didn't want the company,
I guess.

30:38.097 --> 30:41.840
Like I said, I don't know her.

30:45.931 --> 30:47.889
I don't have a sister.

30:47.933 --> 30:50.892
- Her name is Chill Spen.
She's six years younger.

30:50.936 --> 30:57.768
- ♪ Satisfy this hungriness

30:57.812 --> 31:01.163
♪

31:01.207 --> 31:03.339
♪ Let the wind...

31:03.383 --> 31:05.428
- Should have stayed
on the sea.

31:05.472 --> 31:07.822
But then, you struggle staying
in one place, don't you?

31:10.520 --> 31:12.958
There's still
one more knot to untie.

31:15.656 --> 31:17.788
- Might be
a little extra scrutiny, no?

31:17.832 --> 31:19.660
Having Indira Mare on board?

31:19.703 --> 31:21.444
- Hey, hey, how do you think
we got your launch slot

31:21.488 --> 31:23.316
moved up by six weeks, huh?

31:23.359 --> 31:25.231
This is a gift.

31:25.274 --> 31:26.841
- What's the job?

31:26.885 --> 31:29.278
- We want you to bring us home
a Singer.

31:29.322 --> 31:32.847
- You had mentioned making
an encrypted call on your ship.

31:32.891 --> 31:34.283
I tracked it down.

31:34.327 --> 31:36.633
You are the smuggler.

31:36.677 --> 31:40.333
Jate Mura, Tremendous War,
served four tours.

31:40.376 --> 31:42.204
You met in the Pacific,
and then seven years later,

31:42.248 --> 31:44.467
when you started smuggling
black market goods for him.

31:46.992 --> 31:48.689
- Good work, detective.

31:48.732 --> 31:50.560
- Were you working with Strego?

31:50.604 --> 31:52.432
- I wasn't working
with anybody.

31:52.475 --> 31:54.303
The Singer was dropped
at my ship

31:54.347 --> 31:57.306
by a goddamn fake bird.

31:57.350 --> 31:59.395
Doesn't mean
I tried to kill anybody.

31:59.439 --> 32:01.615
Those guys were going at it.

32:01.658 --> 32:03.747
Strego must have found
the Singer

32:03.791 --> 32:06.663
and used it to save himself.

32:06.707 --> 32:08.491
- Hmm.

32:08.535 --> 32:12.713
- Whatever. I'm lying.
It's all lies.

32:12.756 --> 32:15.063
- You're in deeper trouble now.

32:15.107 --> 32:17.761
Your fate lies with the Council
and the people of Moonhaven.

32:20.808 --> 32:22.723
- What will they do to me?

32:29.904 --> 32:32.385
- This...

32:32.428 --> 32:34.387
was your sister's.

32:37.129 --> 32:38.782
A locked box.

32:40.523 --> 32:42.047
Like you--
- Yeah, I get it.

32:53.623 --> 32:56.061
[dramatic music]

32:56.104 --> 32:59.716
all: [chanting] Ho-tee-ta! Tee!

32:59.760 --> 33:06.462
♪

33:11.815 --> 33:14.557
- Prior to the misfortune
on the shuttle,

33:14.601 --> 33:16.472
I had met Bella Sway.

33:16.516 --> 33:18.735
During that exchange,
she had mentioned

33:18.779 --> 33:22.261
making an encrypted call
on her ship.

33:22.304 --> 33:24.524
A further investigation
was required

33:24.567 --> 33:27.048
and revealed
she had been hired

33:27.092 --> 33:28.615
to smuggle our Singer drug

33:28.658 --> 33:30.312
back to Earth.

33:30.356 --> 33:31.835
- It was elementary.

33:34.316 --> 33:36.579
- Bella Sway has since
confessed to the crime.

33:38.929 --> 33:41.062
As to the violent events
that took place on the ship

33:41.106 --> 33:42.803
and those that led up to them,

33:42.846 --> 33:44.979
there is nothing to indicate
that she played a part.

33:50.071 --> 33:53.031
- ♪ Ah
all: ♪ Ah

33:55.381 --> 33:59.907
- Council, speak your mind.

33:59.950 --> 34:01.169
Speak for the light.

34:03.302 --> 34:06.435
- The Singer
is not a drug of choice

34:06.479 --> 34:09.395
to be bought and sold.

34:09.438 --> 34:11.788
To steal it
is to nay understand

34:11.832 --> 34:14.878
the nature of who we are.

34:14.922 --> 34:17.881
The Earther wounds us all.

34:17.925 --> 34:21.146
Wounds that will not close
until the Envoy's guard wakes

34:21.189 --> 34:24.279
and speaks truth.

34:24.323 --> 34:27.717
I say sleep her again,

34:27.761 --> 34:31.460
in our custody,
till the answer's out

34:31.504 --> 34:33.071
and all is known.

34:36.944 --> 34:40.643
- No. No more sleep.

34:40.687 --> 34:43.864
You can't just turn me off
like a switch.

34:43.907 --> 34:45.866
Send me home.

34:45.909 --> 34:47.259
Be rid of me.

34:47.302 --> 34:49.478
- Hear her.

34:49.522 --> 34:52.786
I say let the Mother's justice
sort this out.

34:52.829 --> 34:55.310
She casts only shadow here.

34:55.354 --> 34:58.531
Send her back to Earth.

34:58.574 --> 35:00.359
The gifts of the Bridge
will come to her

35:00.402 --> 35:01.751
in their own time.

35:07.888 --> 35:12.545
- Council, have you more sides
to this shape?

35:12.588 --> 35:14.503
Or shall we rest
with the light of the people?

35:16.810 --> 35:19.508
- ♪ Ah
all: ♪ Ah

35:23.730 --> 35:24.557
- I would like to speak
for the light.

35:29.301 --> 35:31.999
I am a Seeker.

35:32.042 --> 35:34.610
A detective.

35:34.654 --> 35:37.570
My role calls for me
to find the wounds

35:37.613 --> 35:40.094
incurred in this community

35:40.138 --> 35:42.052
and understand how
they may be healed.

35:44.185 --> 35:47.101
Bella Sway has a dark heart.

35:47.145 --> 35:50.626
She killed 72 souls
during the Tremendous War.

35:52.715 --> 35:54.717
She has been captured.

35:54.761 --> 35:57.459
She has been tortured.

35:57.503 --> 35:58.808
She has suffered.

36:00.636 --> 36:02.421
She chose a violent life,

36:02.464 --> 36:05.119
and for that, we bear
no responsibility.

36:05.163 --> 36:08.731
But these instincts rooted
long before that choice.

36:12.082 --> 36:15.434
I share this against the rules
of my calling,

36:15.477 --> 36:18.393
but you must know.

36:18.437 --> 36:21.962
Bella's mother left her
as a baby on Earth

36:22.005 --> 36:23.442
to join us here.

36:25.444 --> 36:27.837
Her blood-sister
was Chill Spen,

36:27.881 --> 36:30.579
the gonesoul from the woods.

36:30.623 --> 36:35.671
I say we are responsible
for her soul-twist.

36:35.715 --> 36:38.370
We have a duty to repair it.

36:38.413 --> 36:39.806
- May I speak?

36:46.378 --> 36:49.119
What does my blood matter?

36:49.163 --> 36:53.385
I'd never set foot on the Glade
until two days ago.

36:53.428 --> 36:55.256
How is it
I should feel something

36:55.300 --> 36:58.303
for people I never even knew?

36:58.346 --> 37:00.174
I'm not from here.

37:02.394 --> 37:04.047
I don't belong here.

37:06.136 --> 37:09.052
- If she feels
no connection to us,

37:09.096 --> 37:11.490
where is our duty to her?

37:14.188 --> 37:15.972
- Then...

37:16.016 --> 37:19.411
forget everything I said.

37:19.454 --> 37:21.369
See the Earther here
before you?

37:23.458 --> 37:26.461
Here on the brink
of the First Wave,

37:26.505 --> 37:30.160
are we to cast her back,
broken and violent,

37:30.204 --> 37:32.293
to the very place
that we've sworn to heal?

37:35.209 --> 37:37.255
We, all of us,
have been raised

37:37.298 --> 37:38.430
to believe in this mission

37:38.473 --> 37:40.083
with all of our hearts
and minds.

37:43.565 --> 37:47.177
If we cannot heal
the dark heart of Bella Sway,

37:47.221 --> 37:49.136
tell me,

37:49.179 --> 37:50.920
how can we ever hope
to succeed?

37:55.229 --> 37:57.579
[crowd murmuring]

38:04.194 --> 38:07.285
If it will please you,

38:07.328 --> 38:08.590
I will make her my charge.

38:10.853 --> 38:12.115
I will open my house.

38:15.771 --> 38:19.297
I will bear full responsibility
for her actions.

38:26.956 --> 38:30.873
- What is Truelune,
if it is not to heal

38:30.917 --> 38:32.266
what has been broken?

38:45.148 --> 38:49.022
- I cannot deny
the light of the people.

38:49.065 --> 38:50.806
The path forward is chosen.

38:53.722 --> 38:55.115
Bella Sway...

38:55.158 --> 38:57.509
[exciting music]

38:57.552 --> 39:00.076
Welcome to Moonhaven.

39:00.120 --> 39:05.343
♪

39:07.693 --> 39:10.260
[footsteps]

39:23.448 --> 39:25.798
- I'm in your cult now, Paul.

39:25.841 --> 39:29.192
You can put flowers in my hair.
We can sing songs.

39:32.021 --> 39:35.285
- I've been taught
when we wound someone,

39:35.329 --> 39:36.983
reparations must be made.

39:37.026 --> 39:39.725
- Pay up.
- Bella.

39:39.768 --> 39:41.422
You owe me.

39:41.466 --> 39:43.032
You're a liar.

39:43.076 --> 39:45.295
You treat trust like a tool.

39:45.339 --> 39:47.428
- I'm broken, remember?

39:47.472 --> 39:49.430
- And what do you break?

39:49.474 --> 39:53.042
Laws. Promises. People.

39:53.086 --> 39:56.872
72 dead. How many others?

39:56.916 --> 39:59.353
How will you pay your debt?

39:59.397 --> 40:01.442
- I owe nothing.

40:01.486 --> 40:03.401
I fought for a cause.

40:03.444 --> 40:06.404
- You fought to keep moving.

40:06.447 --> 40:09.319
You're a coward,
orbiting your darkness.

40:09.363 --> 40:11.321
Spinning around
and never setting down.

40:11.365 --> 40:12.627
- You don't know what you're--

40:12.671 --> 40:14.063
- I didn't fight
to keep you here

40:14.107 --> 40:16.196
so you could be helped.

40:16.239 --> 40:18.416
I fought
so that you can help me.

40:21.680 --> 40:25.292
This place is not a cult.

40:25.335 --> 40:28.121
It's the only way
we'll survive.

40:28.164 --> 40:30.863
And I think it may be
in very real danger.

40:33.518 --> 40:34.997
There's someone
you need to meet.

40:37.522 --> 40:38.523
Get up.

40:51.710 --> 40:53.059
- Who lives here?

40:53.102 --> 40:55.714
- No one anymore.

41:15.516 --> 41:16.517
- Who's that?

41:18.040 --> 41:19.825
- Your sister.

41:19.868 --> 41:22.044
Our custom.

41:22.088 --> 41:25.787
IO assembles the gonesoul
from their living responses.

41:27.572 --> 41:29.922
She is a projection
of your sister,

41:29.965 --> 41:32.402
an Estimator,

41:32.446 --> 41:35.188
not entirely who she was
when she was living,

41:35.231 --> 41:37.712
but enough to gift closure
to those who seek it.

41:41.020 --> 41:43.457
- I can talk to her?

41:43.501 --> 41:46.416
[soft music]

41:46.460 --> 41:53.336
♪

42:07.176 --> 42:09.614
- How now?

42:09.657 --> 42:11.703
How do I know you?

42:11.746 --> 42:14.140
- You don't.

42:14.183 --> 42:15.533
We've never met.

42:22.844 --> 42:25.760
Do you have memories?
- Many.

42:30.156 --> 42:34.769
- Do you remember
going to the woods at night?

42:34.813 --> 42:37.467
- I like to walk in the dark.

42:37.511 --> 42:41.167
The days
are too loud and bright,

42:41.210 --> 42:43.386
but at night, you hear the wind
through the trees.

42:44.910 --> 42:46.607
How they creak-talk

42:46.651 --> 42:48.653
and whisper.

42:48.696 --> 42:53.048
Now, I know it's all wood
and stones and stars, but...

42:53.092 --> 42:54.702
I let my thinks fly.

42:57.096 --> 43:00.316
- Do you remember the night
you met Strego in the woods?

43:00.360 --> 43:02.449
- Which night was that?

43:02.492 --> 43:04.930
They're mixed up now.

43:04.973 --> 43:07.628
My thinks
are in the wrong order.

43:07.672 --> 43:09.064
- It's the one where you died.

43:12.590 --> 43:15.157
Were you meeting someone else
besides Strego?

43:15.201 --> 43:16.419
A third?

43:21.076 --> 43:22.251
Do you remember something?

43:24.340 --> 43:26.516
- Why do you seem so familiar?

43:31.173 --> 43:32.871
- We had the same mother.

43:40.052 --> 43:43.098
Chill.

43:43.142 --> 43:45.274
Did you somehow send for me?

43:50.323 --> 43:52.194
- My sister.

43:52.238 --> 43:54.457
- Yes.

43:54.501 --> 43:56.590
- My sister is Asus.

43:56.634 --> 43:58.636
But it was nice to talk to you.

44:12.084 --> 44:15.261
- I'm sorry
I didn't get here in time.

44:15.304 --> 44:22.224
♪

44:45.421 --> 44:46.901
- Your things.

44:48.860 --> 44:50.165
Figured you might want them.

44:57.912 --> 44:59.609
- I'm bringing trouble for you.

45:01.220 --> 45:02.482
- Trouble is already here.

45:04.484 --> 45:07.095
- Is Fritz upset I'm moving in?

45:07.139 --> 45:08.270
- Very.

45:12.448 --> 45:14.320
- Does he live with you?

45:15.887 --> 45:18.541
- Fritz yearns for Lone.

45:20.543 --> 45:22.850
So he spends time,

45:22.894 --> 45:27.594
little at first,
and then more and more.

45:27.637 --> 45:31.685
He weaves himself
into the family.

45:33.426 --> 45:36.646
And if it holds, he stays.

45:38.431 --> 45:39.562
It's called a Knit.

45:41.347 --> 45:42.565
It's not uncommon.

45:45.525 --> 45:47.179
Lone and I have troubles.

45:49.616 --> 45:50.748
We cool-drift...

45:54.273 --> 45:55.578
Noggin-swirl.

45:57.493 --> 46:00.496
[soft music]

46:00.540 --> 46:01.497
♪

46:01.541 --> 46:02.977
You yearn for the Mother.

46:03.021 --> 46:09.897
♪

46:33.747 --> 46:34.835
- I lied.

46:37.751 --> 46:40.667
After Tomm shot Strego,

46:40.710 --> 46:42.408
he tried to kill me,

46:42.451 --> 46:46.804
so I injected him
with the Singer.

46:46.847 --> 46:48.457
- And why would he do that?

46:50.198 --> 46:52.026
- I saw something
I shouldn't have.

46:54.594 --> 46:57.902
Strego was looking at Tomm
before he died.

46:57.945 --> 47:00.643
I'm sure of it.

47:00.687 --> 47:03.472
He looked at him and said,
"It's done."

47:06.562 --> 47:07.476
- What's done?

47:16.050 --> 47:18.139
Bella,
there may be an agent here

47:18.183 --> 47:22.056
from Earth
trying to destroy everything.

47:22.100 --> 47:23.666
- How do you know it's not me?

47:25.973 --> 47:27.409
- I don't.

47:35.940 --> 47:39.508
- If I help you
figure this out,

47:39.552 --> 47:44.252
you give me my ship back
and let me leave.

47:44.296 --> 47:45.427
- Deal.

48:00.007 --> 48:01.356
- [chuckles]

48:11.758 --> 48:12.933
[box beeps]

48:19.113 --> 48:20.985
- She had my mother's things.

48:32.605 --> 48:33.736
What's that?

48:40.482 --> 48:42.484
- If you're seeing this, Asus,

48:42.528 --> 48:45.270
then know, what we did,
we did for you,

48:45.313 --> 48:47.489
for everyone.

48:47.533 --> 48:50.884
We need to be strong
and protect ourselves.

48:50.928 --> 48:52.712
They lied to us.

48:52.755 --> 48:54.801
We were never going
to save the Earth.

48:54.844 --> 48:56.716
The Bridge is a trap.

48:56.759 --> 48:58.718
[dramatic music]

49:01.939 --> 49:03.157
Somebody's out there.
They've been watching me.

49:03.201 --> 49:04.985
The transport ships
that land today

49:05.029 --> 49:06.769
will take the First Wave
back to Earth.

49:06.813 --> 49:08.336
The bridge is safe.

49:08.380 --> 49:09.642
[ Spaceship whooshing ]

49:09.685 --> 49:11.731
A device for extracting the
mark.

49:11.774 --> 49:14.821
So many.
Why would people take them out?

49:14.864 --> 49:17.650
Speak your name.
Indira Mare.

49:17.693 --> 49:19.739
You're gonna be the Envoy,
you know?

49:19.782 --> 49:22.002
Those ships must be allowed to
land.

49:22.046 --> 49:23.699
She has the will of her people.

49:23.743 --> 49:25.832
I can't force her to act.

49:25.875 --> 49:27.834
[ Dramatic music plays ]

49:27.877 --> 49:29.967
♪

49:32.534 --> 49:35.407
[gentle music]

49:35.450 --> 49:42.370
♪
